    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Job Description Parser\\n\",\"**NLP Project 26 of 100** — Extract skills, experience requirements, location, and salary hints from job postings.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Use regex + NER for structured extraction from JDs.\\n\",\"2. Handle varied formats and inconsistent text.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, re, spacy\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\ntry: nlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nexcept:\\n    import subprocess, sys\\n    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','spacy','download','en_core_web_sm'])\\n    nlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"JDS = [\\n    'Senior Python Developer — Remote. 5+ years experience in Python, Django, AWS. Salary: $120K-$150K. Skills: Python, SQL, Docker, CI/CD.',\\n    'Machine Learning Engineer in San Francisco. Requirements: 3+ years ML, PyTorch, TensorFlow. MS preferred. Competitive salary + equity.',\\n    'Data Scientist (NYC) — 2-4 years experience. Skills needed: Python, R, SQL, Tableau. $90K-$110K base. Bachelor in CS or Statistics.',\\n]\\n\\ndef parse_jd(text):\\n    result = {}\\n    # Experience\\n    m = re.search(r'(\\\\d+)\\\\+?\\\\s*(?:years?|yrs?)', text, re.IGNORECASE)\\n    result['min_experience'] = int(m.group(1)) if m else None\\n    # Salary\\n    m = re.findall(r'\\\\$([\\\\d,]+)K?', text)\\n    result['salary_range'] = [int(s.replace(',','')) for s in m] if m else None\\n    # Location\\n    doc = nlp(text)\\n    locations = [e.text for e in doc.ents if e.label_ == 'GPE']\\n    result['location'] = locations[0] if locations else ('Remote' if 'remote' in text.lower() else None)\\n    # Skills\\n    skills_pattern = r'\\\\b(?:Python|Java|JavaScript|SQL|R|Docker|AWS|GCP|Azure|PyTorch|TensorFlow|Django|React|Tableau|CI/CD)\\\\b'\\n    result['skills'] = list(set(re.findall(skills_pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE)))\\n    # Degree\\n    degree_pattern = r'\\\\b(?:Bachelor|Master|MS|BS|PhD|MBA)\\\\b'\\n    result['degree'] = list(set(re.findall(degree_pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE)))\\n    return result\\n\\nfor i, jd in enumerate(JDS):\\n    print(f'\\\\nJD {i+1}: {jd[:60]}...')\\n    parsed = parse_jd(jd)\\n    for k, v in parsed.items():\\n        print(f'  {k}: {v}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Regex + NER effectively parses structured job descriptions.**\\n\",\"- **Skills extraction uses a curated dictionary** of technical terms.\\n\",\"- **Salary and experience parsing handles common formats.**\\n\",\"- **For production, train a custom model** on diverse JD formats.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
